{
  "stem": "3360.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One of them was extremely well set and, and in very good financial circumstances, I should say.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- excuse me-- and she urged my father to start writing to, to him-- to her-- excuse-- to him, her husband, Oscar Wolf and Minna Wolf.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- excuse me-- I don't know if he actually did right away.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He may have, like, put it in maybe sort of veiled language in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My mother was adamant about the fact, that it was her intuition that this was going to last, that it was going to get worse, and that the only-- the only hope we would have is by getting out of the country.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, there are other people who left right away, in '33, but very few--",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--at that time.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, did not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Anyway, excuse me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The-- as the years went on, and as the laws that the Nazis passed became worse and worse, and after, after the Kristallnacht, you just knew you had to get out.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Everybody knew that they had to get out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But everybody could not get out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was no country that opened its doors like the United States did when Russia invaded Hungary, if you recall that-- came in with tanks to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the United States opened its doors and let the Hungarians in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Nobody opened their doors for the Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It, it was a-- an unbelievably pathetic, sad chapter in history.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
